BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:stimuleringsfonds-international-vouchers-2026@artificialnouveau.github.
 io
DTSTAMP:20260710T094439Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261027
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261028
SUMMARY:Deadline: International Vouchers
DESCRIPTION:Travel voucher for Dutch-based professionals in design\, archit
 ecture and/or digital culture who have been invited by a foreign party to 
 give a presentation\, lecture or workshop. To apply you must have submitte
 d an application to the Fund in the past five years that was positively as
 sessed. Round 2 (4 May to 22 June 2026) has now closed. Round 3 is the cur
 rent round: it runs 8 September 2026 15:00 CEST to 27 October 2026 16:00 C
 EST\, with a budget of €33\,000.\n\nOrganisation: Stimuleringsfonds Crea
 tieve Industrie (Creative Industries Fund NL)\nLocation: Netherlands (for 
 international travel)\nAward: Up to €1\,500 within Europe (zone 1) / up 
 to €2\,500 outside Europe (zone 2)\nDuration: Per trip\n\nMore: https://
 www.stimuleringsfonds.nl/en/grants/international-vouchers?utm_source=artif
 icialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.stimuleringsfonds.nl/en/grants/international-vouchers?utm_s
 ource=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Netherlands (for international travel)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:rijkscultuurfondsen-interdisciplinary-grant-2026@artificialnouveau.gith
 ub.io
DTSTAMP:20260710T094439Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261001
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261002
SUMMARY:Deadline: Rijkscultuurfondsen: Interdisciplinary Grant
DESCRIPTION:The Interdisciplinary grant is a new joint scheme of the six Du
 tch national cultural funds (Mondriaan Fund\, Performing Arts Fund NL\, Fu
 nd for Cultural Participation\, Netherlands Film Fund\, Creative Industrie
 s Fund NL\, and the Dutch Foundation for Literature)\, announced on 7 July
  2026. It supports makers and organisations whose work genuinely crosses t
 he boundaries of the individual funds' disciplines (visual art\, design\, 
 film\, literature\, performing arts\, and cultural participation) and cann
 ot be contained within a single discipline. TWO TRACKS: an Individual trac
 k for professional makers with a demonstrable interdisciplinary practice (
 at least one year of experience\; income cap EUR 55\,000 including the gra
 nt\; approximately EUR 24\,900 for 12 months)\; and an Organisation track 
 for organisations running multi-discipline projects. AMOUNT: EUR 12\,500 t
 o 50\,000 per project. ELIGIBILITY: makers and organisations based in the 
 Netherlands or the Caribbean part of the Kingdom. APPLYING: handled throug
 h the Mondriaan Fund's online application portal (info@mondriaanfonds.nl)\
 ; an account is required in advance. DEADLINE: 1 October 2026\, 16:00 Dutc
 h time (single application round).\n\nOrganisation: Dutch national cultura
 l funds (Rijkscultuurfondsen)\, via the Mondriaan Fund\nLocation: Netherla
 nds. For professional makers and organisations based in the Netherlands or
  the Caribbean part of the Kingdom whose practice spans multiple disciplin
 es.\nAward: EUR 12\,500 to 50\,000 per project. The individual-maker track
  is approximately EUR 24\,900 for 12 months (income cap EUR 55\,000 includ
 ing the grant).\nDuration: Up to 12 months for the individual-maker track.
 \n\nMore: https://www.mondriaanfonds.nl/en/apply-for-a-grant/grants/interd
 isciplinary/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.mondriaanfonds.nl/en/apply-for-a-grant/grants/interdiscipli
 nary/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Netherlands. For professional makers and organisations based in th
 e Netherlands or the Caribbean part of the Kingdom whose practice spans mu
 ltiple disciplines.
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
